            "answer_text": "[math]x(x - 1)(x + 1) = 990[/math] [math]\\implies x(x - 1) (x + 1) = 10 (9) (11)[/math] [math]\\text{x = 10 is a solution of the equation.}[/math] [math]\\text{ Let us find all the solutions algebraically.}[/math] [math]x (x - 1) (x + 1) = 990[/math] [math]\\implies x (x^2 - 1) - 990 = 0[/math] [math]\\implies x^3 - x - 990 = 0[/math] [math]\\implies x^3 - 10 x^2 + 10 x^2 - 100 x + 99 x - 990 = 0[/math] [math]\\implies x^2 (x - 10) + 10 x (x - 10) + 99 (x - 10) = 0[/math] [math]\\implies (x - 10) (x^2 + 10 x + 99) = 0[/math] [math]\\implies x - 10 = 0\\implies x = 10[/math] [math]\\text{Or}[/math] [math]x^2 + 10 x + 99 = 0[/math] [math]\\text{We use quadratic formula to solve this equation.}[/math] [math]x = \\dfrac{- 10 \\pm\\sqrt{100 - 396}}{2}[/math] [math]\\implies x =\\dfrac{- 10 \\pm 2 \\sqrt{- 74}}{2}[/math] [math]\\implies x = - 5\\pm \\sqrt{74}\\,\\,i[/math] ",
